It is not acceptable to dismiss the feelings of a woman when she expresses her dissatisfaction with your behavior. It is not okay to demand her trust when you have repeatedly lied and betrayed her. Saying "I love you" does not excuse the way you have made her feel worthless and belittled. If you truly missed her, you would make an effort to be present in her life. It is unfair to expect a woman to be faithful to you when you are not committing to a relationship or being honest about your intentions. Using the excuse of being human and imperfect as a justification for cheating, lying, and emotionally abusing her is unacceptable. Apologizing is not enough, you need to take action to change your behavior.⁠
⁠
Additionally, it is important to respect a woman's journey towards self-love and healing. Attempting to distract her from this process or hindering her progress is not acceptable. If you have caused her pain and suffering, the best thing you can do is leave her alone and give her space to heal and move on. It is not okay to continue to inflict harm and cause further emotional distress.⁠
⁠
___________________________⁠
⁠

To the woman reading this, I want you to know that despite feeling lonely and going through heartbreak, something good will come your way. You deserve nothing but the best and no amount of betrayal or heartache will change that. You will find someone who is genuine and willing to match your efforts in a relationship. It is important to remember that the end of a relationship is not the end of your journey. It may be difficult, but you will find the strength and courage to start again.⁠
⁠
I want to take a moment to express my gratitude towards you for being strong and brave. You have faced difficult times with resilience and determination. You have fought for what you deserve and have inspired others to do the same. Your strength is admirable and I want you to know that it does not go unnoticed. You are worthy of love and happiness and it will come to you when the time is right. Keep your head held high and keep moving forward.⁠
⁠
⁠
___________________________⁠

Walking away from a difficult situation or a person who has been causing harm is not always an easy or immediate process. It can take time and effort to come to the decision to leave and to actually make it happen. It is important to remember that it is not a sign of weakness to hold on to someone who has been hurting you. In fact, it takes a lot of strength to continue to care for someone, despite the pain they have caused.⁠
⁠
It's likely that over time you have built up the courage to fall for this person, and with time and support, you will build up the courage to walk away from them. It's important to understand that the process of healing takes time. It's important to give yourself the time and space you need to heal, process and make decisions about your relationship.⁠
⁠
It's also important to remember that walking away doesn't mean giving up on love, but rather recognizing that the relationship is not healthy and not worth continuing. It's important to surround yourself with supportive people and to seek professional help if needed. Keep in mind that you deserve to be in a healthy and loving relationship, and that you have the power to make choices that will lead you to that kind of relationship.⁠
______________________⁠
⁠
⁠

Love is real; it is more than a dream you've had. It is more than an idea. Love exists, and it can be cultivated only in a relationship with someone willing to match your effort, but only after you've mastered the ability to love yourself. Self-love not only creates a standard for which you are to be loved, but the mastery of self-love ensures that you will be capable of loving the person who falls in love with you. ⁠
⁠
@Samantha.King.Holmes, I have seen every layer of who you are, and my love for you has continued to grow and evolve along with our relationship. The coolest thing for me is that I've gotten to love you in a way that no one ever has, I know you in ways that no one else does. I have been your admirer, your boyfriend, your collaborator, your advocate, a cheerleader, a husband, and now we're parents to two beautiful children. You are a teacher, I learn from you. My lover, a place in which I've found solace and inspiration. My friend, there for me when I had nothing, here beside me to share in the sum of it all. ⁠
⁠
I truly understand how blessed I am to find love and to be loved in a way that makes me want to try even harder to prove that I am worthy of your energy and time. I've been thinking a lot about what love really means and the older I get, the more profound the meaning, and while it is difficult to sum up in words, tonight, at this moment, I believe love to be without conditions. I love you even on my toughest days, even on your toughest days. Love is kind, and though I'm not always smiling, I try my best to extend some act of kindness just to let you know that are not alone in this. Love protects the other person both physically and mentally. When I say I love you, part of that means that I ensure no harm comes your way and that you are free to dwell in a mind filled with peace and a heart that doesn't feel as if it needs to hold back.⁠
⁠
@Samantha.King.Holmes, I appreciate all the ways you've managed to teach me what it means to be in a relationship, what it means to be married, and what it means to have a friendship with the one who has your heart. I say all of this to say, " I LOVE YOU." Happy Valentines Day.

Wherever you are, whatever you’re doing whenever you read this…I hope you’re beginning to see the beauty in being without the people who hurt your heart. Life begins to bloom when you begin to practice self love in the absence of those who tried to break you. 

Okay, back to the real world. Be safe.

If there's one thing I want you to know, it's this: self-love is one of the most beautiful gifts you can give yourself. It's easy to think that our happiness and fulfillment lie in external sources - in our achievements, in the approval of others, in the material possessions we accumulate. But the truth is, everything we've ever needed has been within us all along.⁠
When we take the time to truly love ourselves, to embrace all of our quirks and flaws, we open up a world of possibility. We begin to see ourselves in a different light - as deserving of love and respect, just as we are. And with that shift in perspective comes a newfound confidence, a sense of purpose, and a deep sense of inner peace.⁠
⁠
The journey of self-discovery can be challenging at times, but the rewards are immeasurable. As you learn to love and accept yourself, you'll begin to attract more positivity and abundance into your life. You'll form deeper, more meaningful relationships, and you'll feel empowered to pursue your passions and dreams without fear.⁠
⁠
So I encourage you to take some time for yourself today/tonight/thisweek - to reflect on all the wonderful things that make you who you are, and to embrace them fully. Remember that everything you need to live a happy, fulfilled life is already within you.

Today is my Birthday; this is year 34.⁠
⁠
I have spent the better part of my life in service to those I care about and love. Longevity is one of my favorite words, and I am blessed to have had so much time to practice that in everything that I do, from friendships to relationships and my career. ⁠
⁠
I wanted to share some of what I learned (see the posts above) in hopes of providing some sort of guidance or inspiration. Some of you have been here since 2012, reading these words, these posts, and ideas, and some of you are new; maybe you've just discovered this account, and so I hope this gives you a bit of insight as to who I am and what my intentions are.⁠
⁠
I'm a person who still believes in the most honest love; I am a person who believes that vulnerability is a beautiful art form and that loyalty and kindness are true strengths and indications of discipline. I believe that despite this current time of fear when it comes to love and this idea of playing games to avoid getting hurt that behind all of that, there are still people willing to love in a way that makes life a bit more beautiful.⁠
⁠
I hope you're healing wherever you are. I hope you're taking steps toward living a life you can be proud of, and I hope you're actively walking away from what no longer deserves your energy. I hope you grow, I hope the obstacles make you stronger. I hope the heartache provides you with more wisdom. I hope the person who needed to read this sees this for what it is, a message, a sign.⁠
⁠
Aries, I hope I make you proud. Birthday twins, I feel you, I see you. Happy Birthday to us.⁠
⁠
Life is for the living, be careful not to do things that will cause it to end. ⁠
⁠
Protect your time, your heart, your energy, and your spirit. Take care.

Bonus: Ways to deal with a partner who may be gaslighting you.

Educate yourself: Learn about gaslighting, its signs, and its impact on your mental health. Understanding this manipulation tactic will help you recognize when it's happening to you.

Trust your intuition: Pay attention to your gut feelings and emotions. If something feels off, don't dismiss it. Trust yourself, and remember that your feelings are valid.

Seek support: Reach out to friends, family, or a mental health professional to discuss your concerns. Having a support network can help you navigate the complexities of a gaslighting relationship.

Set boundaries: Establish and maintain clear boundaries with your partner. Communicate your limits, and don't be afraid to stand your ground when they are crossed.

Plan your exit: If the relationship continues to be toxic and harmful, prioritize your well-being by planning a safe exit. Seek assistance from loved ones or professionals to ensure your safety and emotional support during this difficult process.

Heartbreak…

Walking away from a difficult situation or a person who has been causing harm is not always an easy or immediate process. It can take time and effort to come to the decision to leave and to actually make it happen. It is important to remember that it is not a sign of weakness to hold on to someone who has been hurting you. In fact, it takes a lot of strength to continue to care for someone, despite the pain they have caused.

It's likely that over time you have built up the courage to fall for this person, and with time and support, you will build up the courage to walk away from them. It's important to understand that the process of healing takes time. It's important to give yourself the time and space you need to heal, process and make decisions about your relationship.

It's also important to remember that walking away doesn't mean giving up on love, but rather recognizing that the relationship is not healthy and not worth continuing. 

It's important to surround yourself with supportive people and to seek professional help if needed. Keep in mind that you deserve to be in a healthy and loving relationship, and that you have the power to make choices that will lead you to that kind of relationship.
Choose peace.
A person's inability to remain faithful is a reflection of their character, not a measure of your worth; never blame yourself for the choices they made to betray your trust.

A narcissist possesses an inflated sense of self-importance and a deep need for excessive attention and admiration. They often lack empathy for others and possess a fragile self-esteem. To maintain their elevated self-image, narcissists engage in various behaviors that can cause self-doubt in those around them.

Gaslighting: One of the most damaging techniques used by narcissists is gaslighting, a form of psychological manipulation. Through this tactic, a narcissist will deny or distort facts, making the victim question their perception, memory, or reality itself. Over time, the victim may doubt their sanity.

Constant Criticism: Narcissists frequently criticize and belittle others. They might pick on their victim's slightest mistakes, making them feel inadequate or worthless. This constant barrage can erode the victim's confidence over time.

Comparisons: Narcissists often compare their victims to others in unfavorable ways, making them feel as if they're always falling short. This can cause the victim to perpetually feel as if they're not good enough.

Projecting: Narcissists project their own insecurities and faults onto others. For example, if they're being deceitful, they might accuse the victim of lying.
